&lt;h1 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Introduction&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Polar codes were introduced by Erdal ArÄ±kan in 2009 and they provide the first deterministic construction of capacity-achieving codes for binary memoryless symmetric (BMS) channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Notice that there is only one channel to transmission data, in order to facilitate the understanding, we logically separate one channel to two channel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img data-src=&#34;http://imgcdn.gality.cn/blog/c0vryg.png&#34; alt=&#34;Figure 1&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
